Articles.Content:
On 1/17/2019 at 4:26 AM, Drakenex said:

Thanks!

 

Enjoy

@alberro+ Drakenex made a black alternate skin on Page 9, and it shouldn't be too difficult to make a metallic variant. If you're just looking for another variant, I'd make a copy of the default textures, gray it out a little, maybe play with edge highlights and then set it up as a texture variant. If you're looking for something reflective with TU, that shouldn't be too difficult either, but I'd set it up as a separate part so you can still swap between the white/black without the reflective stuff. I don't know enough about TU to know if you can make a reflective variant with non-reflective variants.

Is the ICPS (with the Orion) supposed to only have a TWR of 0.35 in vacuum?

12 hours ago, Contrabass Ophicleide said:

Is the ICPS (with the Orion) supposed to only have a TWR of 0.35 in vacuum?

Most upper stages have less than 1.0 TWR. The RL-10 is no exception with its ridiculously low TWR, but it makes up for it with efficiency. That's the draw back. Do you want:

Fast acceleration for short time

Or

Slow acceleration for really long time

That's why you have these powerful first stages that last for a long time. By the time the upper stage takes over, the orbit is almost circular or is so high the upper stage doesn't have much work to do.
